defs.name: RestrictedStorage
defs.docs:
Similar to a `MaskedStorage` and a `Storage` combined, but restricts usage
 to only getting and modifying the components. That means it's not possible to
 modify the inner bitset so the iteration cannot be invalidated. In other words,
 no insertion or removal is allowed.

Builds an immutable `RestrictedStorage` out of a `Storage`. Allows deferred

defs.value:

                  SequentialRestriction>
defs.docs:
Builds a mutable `RestrictedStorage` out of a `Storage`. Allows restricted
 access to the inner components without allowing invalidating the
 bitset for iteration in `Join`.

defs.name: par_restrict_mut
defs.value:
fn <'rf> (&'rf mut self) -> RestrictedStorage<'rf, 'st, T, &mut T::Storage, &BitSet,
                  MutableParallelRestriction>
defs.docs:
Builds a mutable, parallel `RestrictedStorage`,
 does not allow mutably getting other components
 aside from the current iteration.

defs.name: is_alive

Checks if an entity is alive.
 Please note that atomically created or deleted entities
 (the ones created / deleted with the `Entities` struct)
 are not handled by this method. Therefore, you
 should have called `maintain()` before using this
 method.

defs.name: maintain
defs.docs:
Merges in the appendix, recording all the dynamically created
 and deleted entities into the persistent generations vector.
 Also removes all the abandoned components.
